comments.body:
Hi,

@flouthoc in the end I don't know if I was clear, but here I am looking for the same as what buildx does. buildx accepts `--output type=local,dest=/some/dir` and no matter where the actual docker deamon is, the final output file will be on the machine where the client runs.

In principle do you agree this is the "right" machine where to output things ? If yes and if it's not something extremly hard to implement in podman (you know the code thousands times better than me), I may have a look to try to implement this myself.
